3384	\subsection{The unit square (D2$'$): a mate-calculus telescope}
3385	
3386	The proof of \cref{lem:pullback_tensor_iso_unit} bottoms out in the single morphism equation
3387	labelled the \emph{unit square} below. Its proof is a telescope across three nested adjunction
3388	layers (sheafification, presheaf pullback--pushforward, sheaf pullback--pushforward). This
3389	subsection isolates the load-bearing intermediate identities as named lemmas so each can be
3390	discharged independently, then assembles them.
3391	
3392	We fix throughout a morphism of schemes \(f : Y \to X\) and write
3393	\(\varphi = f.\mathtt{toRingCatSheafHom}\), \(\varphi' = \varphi.\mathrm{hom}\). Let \(a_X, a_Y\)
3394	denote sheafification of presheaves of modules on \(X\), \(Y\); \(\mathbf{1}^{\mathrm{p}}\) the
3395	presheaf monoidal unit; \(F = \mathtt{pullback}\,\varphi'\) the presheaf pullback;
3396	\(\eta\,F : F.\mathrm{obj}\,\mathbf{1}^{\mathrm{p}} \to \mathbf{1}^{\mathrm{p}}\) its oplax unit
3397	comparison; and \(\varepsilon(G)\) the lax unit comparison of a lax monoidal functor \(G\). The
3398	isomorphisms \(\mathtt{pullbackValIso}\,f\,\mathcal{O}_X\) and \(\mathtt{sheafifyUnitIso}\) are
3399	the file's comparison morphisms relating the sheaf-level pullback value to the sheafification of
3400	the presheaf-level pullback. Write
3401	\(\mathtt{sheafCounit}_\bullet = (\mathtt{sheafificationAdjunction}\,(\mathbf{1}_{\bullet.\mathtt{ringCatSheaf}.\mathrm{val}})).\mathrm{counit}\).
3402	
3403	\begin{lemma}\leanok
3404	[Presheaf-side unit mate identity]
3405	  \label{lem:presheaf_unit_comp_map_eta}
3406	  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.Modules.presheafUnit_comp_map_eta}
3407	  \uses{lem:presheaf_pushforward_laxmonoidal, lem:presheaf_pullback_oplaxmonoidal}
3408	  At the presheaf level the pullback--pushforward adjunction unit at the monoidal unit,
3409	  post-composed with the pushforward of the oplax unit comparison, recovers the lax unit:
3410	  \[
3411	    \mathtt{presheafAdj}.\mathrm{unit}.\mathrm{app}\,\mathbf{1}^{\mathrm{p}}
3412	      \;\mathbin{;}\;
3413	      (\mathtt{pushforward}\,\varphi').\mathrm{map}\,(\eta\,F)
3414	      \;=\; \varepsilon(\mathtt{pushforward}\,\varphi'),
3415	  \]
3416	  where \(\mathtt{presheafAdj} = \mathtt{pullbackPushforwardAdjunction}\,\varphi'\) is the
3417	  presheaf pullback--pushforward adjunction and \(F = \mathtt{pullback}\,\varphi'\).
3418	\end{lemma}
3419	
3420	\begin{proof}
3421	  \uses{lem:presheaf_pushforward_laxmonoidal, lem:presheaf_pullback_oplaxmonoidal}
3422	  This is Mathlib's general adjunction-mate identity
3423	  \(\mathtt{Adjunction.unit\_app\_unit\_comp\_map\_}\eta\) instantiated at the presheaf
3424	  pullback--pushforward adjunction \(\mathtt{pullbackPushforwardAdjunction}\,\varphi'\). That
3425	  identity holds for any adjunction whose left adjoint is oplax monoidal and whose right adjoint
3426	  is lax monoidal in a mate-compatible way. The compatible pair is
3427	  \(\mathtt{presheafPushforwardLaxMonoidal}\)
3428	  (\cref{lem:presheaf_pushforward_laxmonoidal}) and \(\mathtt{presheafPullbackOplaxMonoidal}\)
3429	  (\cref{lem:presheaf_pullback_oplaxmonoidal}), so the
3430	  mate identity applies to the concrete adjunction and yields the stated equation.
3431	\end{proof}
